              <div style=3D"text-align: left;">Not sure how to measure Appa=
rel?</div>
<div style=3D"text-align: left;"></div>
<div style=3D"text-align: left;">When shopping for clothing online, knowing=
 your measurements will help you select the best size for your body without=
 trying the product on. Because there are so many fits for different types =
of clothing, we've created a clothing size chart for reference. Please see =
directions below for how to measure each respective part of your body.</div=
>
<div style=3D"text-align: left;">
<ul>
<li>
<span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">Chest/Bust</span><span> </span>=
- Keep the tape parallel to the floor and measure around the fullest part o=
f your chest/bust. Use this measurement for tops and dresses.</li>
<li>
<span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">Hips </span>- Measure the fulle=
st part of your hips standing with your feet together. Make sure to measure=
 over your buttocks as well.</li>
<li>
<span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">Inseam</span><span> </span>- Me=
asure from the crotch to the inside seam of the leg while wearing your best=
 fitting pair of pants. Wearing shoes is recommended to make sure the lengt=
h is correct for you. Measure to the 1/2".</li>
<li>
<span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">Neck</span> - U.S. dress shirts=
 are use inches for neck measurements. Wrap the tape around the Adam's appl=
e. Make sure the tape is consistently level all the way around your neck.</=
li>
</ul>
</div>
